# File headers (MIT)

Every **new** committable source/config/script file must include a header.

## Exceptions (no header required)

- `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `tsconfig.json` (JSON, no comments)
- `LICENSE` (full MIT text already present)
- `.gitignore` (optional one-line comment only)
- Generated `dist/` (not committed)

## Entry file (`src/index.ts`) — full MIT block

```typescript
#!/usr/bin/env node
/**
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * Package : @raviraj87/<package-name>
 * File    : index.ts
 * Purpose : <one-line description>
 *
 * Copyright (c) 2026 Ravi Raj
 * ...full MIT license text...
 * SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 */
```

## All other TypeScript / JavaScript

```typescript
/**
 * @raviraj87/<package-name> · <filename>
 * <One-line purpose describing this file's responsibility.>
 *
 * Copyright (c) 2026 Ravi Raj · MIT License · see LICENSE
 */
```

## YAML / `.env.example`

```yaml
# @raviraj87/<package-name> · config.example.yaml
# <One-line purpose>
#
# Copyright (c) 2026 Ravi Raj · MIT License · see LICENSE
```

## Rules

- Replace `<package-name>` and purpose per repo/file.
- Do not remove headers when editing.
- Keep purpose accurate when file responsibility changes.
